tweet_raw: **Brett Harrison** a name that bridges the gap between two distinct financial realms: 🔥🔥🔥👇👇👇🍿🍿🍿**Wall Street** and the **crypto market**. Lets delve into this intriguing connection.1. **Citadel and FTX**:   - **Citadel LLC** is a well-known hedge fund while **Citadel Securities** stands as a major market maker for stock brokers. Both entities were founded and are predominantly owned by **Ken Griffin** Citadels CEO.   - Similarly **FTX** is a prominent cryptocurrency exchange and **Alameda Research** serves as its private equity counterpart. Both were founded by **Sam Bankman-Fried**.   - The parallel here lies in the shared figure of **Brett Harrison**.2. **Who Is Brett Harrison?**:   - Harrison like many Wall Street luminaries made the leap into the crypto space. His journey began at **Citadel Securities** where he held dual roles:       - **Head of Exchange-Traded Fund (ETF) Technology**       - **Head of Semi-Systematic Technology**   - At Citadel he led teams in managing quantitative trading strategies and optimizing profits.   - Notably Harrison left Citadel Securities during its controversial involvement in the **GameStop saga**.   - His next move? **FTX.US** where he became the first president of the U.S.-based company.   - This reunion with **Sam Bankman-Fried** marked their collaboration since their days at **Jane Street**.3. **Common Threads**:   - **Harrison** acts as a common thread linking **FTX** and **Citadel**.   - The line between traditional finance and the crypto world continues to blur and the **FTX saga** has accelerated this collision of two worlds according to **Ken Griffin** Citadels CEO¹.In this intricate dance of finance Brett Harrisons role underscores the interconnectedness of seemingly disparate domains. 🌐💼🚀#AMCSource: 13/02/2024(1) One Man Connects FTX Citadel and the Crypto Market Crash. investorplace.com/2022/12/on….(2) Citadels Griffin Calls FTX Blow-up a Travesty in Financial History. markets.businessinsider.com/…

I doxxed myself and they still respected my takes on the market despite being a girl on the internet. That lil private sub was all I needed. I would’ve never doxxed in web3 if those same degens didn’t bring me here and they’re all still among my closest and best friends. We’ve all come a long way since 2021. Whether it’s in an NFT collection alpha group people you picked up along the way you literally can’t stick around without *your* community. It saved me after moving to the burbs being a first-time parent and being isolated during the pandemic. The power of the internet community got me to drop what I was doing to help nurture that here in web3. The people are truly the alpha. It changed my entire life. I’m seeing lots of intensity on the tl lately but lots of amazing positive energy to balance that. Here for more collaboration connection and positivity in web3 I really feel like this I what I was made to do.
